_We may vary this schedule, depending on the needs of the class.  If you miss a class, it's your responsibility to find out what you've missed._

*GENETIC DETERMINISM*
week 1
- local optima
- environment and inheritance
- _no class_

week 2
- biology as ideology: multiple causation
- biology as ideology: tuberculosis
- theory really matters: biological determinism --- with guest star Paul Griffiths

*THE RECEIVED VIEW OF EVOLUTION*
week 3
- life before Darwin
- Darwin
- diversity

week 4
- natural selection
- units of selection
- selection and evolution

*THE GENE'S EYE VIEW OF EVOLUTION*
week 5
- _no class_
- the active germ-line replicator (Dawkins)
- the genetic code (Nirenberg)

week 6
- replicators and interactors
- the special status of replicators
- the bookkeeping argument

week 7
- the extended phenotype
- the extended phenotype (Dawkins)
- the extended phenotype (examples and conclusions)


week 8
- recap
*THE ORGANISM STRIKES BACK*
- _no class_
- introduction to the history of genetics (Pontecorvo etc.)

week 9
- are genes real? (Comfort)
- genes are active germ line replicators
- genes are difference makers

week 10
*ORGANISMS, GROUPS, AND SUPERORGANISMS*
- interactors / altruism
- group selection
- population-structured evolution

week 11
*SPECIES*
- are species real?
- the nature of species
- the one true tree of life / clay life and sub-subsoil life

week 12
- species selection
*WEIRD LIFE*
- artificial life: possibilities
- artificial life: are we living in a computer simulation?

week 13
- defining life / universal biology
- xenobiology: theory
- xenobiology: possibilities
